This is simple matter of evaluating an integral. From the definition of
the average value of a function on an interval, we can write an
expression for the average value of $1/x$ on the interval $[1,e]$:

\begin{align*}
f_{avg} &= \frac{1}{e - 1}\int_{1}^{e}\frac{1}{x}\,dx \\ &= \frac{1}{e - 1}\ln(x)\Big\vert_{1}^{e}
\\f_{avg} &= \frac{1}{e - 1}
\end{align*}

So the average value of $1/x$ on the interval $[1,e]$ is $(e - 1)^{-1}$.
